post_cb({"bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_45902923_45903381_1": {"length": 14, "quality": 0.9333333333333333, "section_id": 3228}}, "n3337": {"so_45902923_45903381_1": {"length": 14, "quality": 0.9333333333333333, "section_id": 3101}}, "n4659": {"so_45902923_45903381_1": {"length": 14, "quality": 0.9333333333333333, "section_id": 3985}}}, "45902923": {"ViewCount": "144", "Body": "<p>Is the following generic (polymorphic) lambda legal C++14?</p>\n<pre><code>auto f = [](auto x[3]) {\n    x[0];\n    x[1];\n    // etc.\n};\n</code></pre>\n<p>GCC and Clang 4 accept the code, but Visual Studio 2017 does not. Is it legal?</p>\n<pre><code>error C3318: 'auto [3]': an array cannot have an element type that contains 'auto'\n</code></pre>\n", "AcceptedAnswerId": "45903381", "Title": "Generic lambdas with statically sized arrays as arguments", "CreationDate": "2017-08-27T08:10:09.387", "Id": "45902923", "CommentCount": "0", "LastEditDate": "2017-08-27T09:03:14.547", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastEditorUserId": "4672588", "LastActivityDate": "2017-08-27T09:08:35.853", "Score": "7", "OwnerUserId": "116186", "Tags": "<c++><c++14><generic-lambda>", "AnswerCount": "1"}, "45903381": {"Id": "45903381", "PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<p>It is illegal.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://eel.is/c++draft/dcl.array#1.sentence-1\" rel=\"noreferrer\">[dcl.array]/1</a>, emphasis mine:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_45902923_45903381_0\">In a declaration T D where D has the form</p>\n<pre>D1 [ <i>constant-expression</i><sub>opt</sub> ] <i>attribute-specifier-seq</i><sub>opt</sub></pre>\n<p id=\"so_45902923_45903381_1\">and the type of the identifier in the declaration <code>T D1</code> is \u201c<em>derived-declarator-type-list</em> <code>T</code>\u201d, then the type of the identifier of <code>D</code> is an array type; <strong>if the type of the identifier of <code>D</code> contains the <code>auto</code> <em>type-specifier</em>, the program is ill-formed.</strong></p>\n</blockquote>\n", "LastActivityDate": "2017-08-27T09:08:35.853", "CommentCount": "5", "CreationDate": "2017-08-27T09:08:35.853", "ParentId": "45902923", "Score": "9", "OwnerUserId": "4672588"}});